Water Quality

Overall Physio-Chemical WFD

Water quality is one of the three pillars of the ecological trinity of river health, alongside physical habitat and flow. You can have a river with perfect physical habitat and with natural annual flow, but if its water is polluted it won’t realise its true ecological potential.

Within the Parrett’s 51 individual EA waterbodies.

In the most recent WFD classification in 2022, 16% of waterbodies scored “Good” for Physio-Chemical Quality Elements. Whilst 2% of waterbodies scored “High”.

Physio-Chemical Quality Elements include the following items:

- Physio-Chemical Quality Elements
- Ammonia (Phys-Chemical)
- Dissolved oxygen
- Temperature
- Biochemical Overall Oxygen Demand (BOD)
- Phosphate
- pH
- Acid Neutralising Capacity
